Description: Substantial fragment, made up of six joining sherds, of East Greek pottery stemmed dish; inside slipped cream; key maeander on top of rim; band of tongues (some red) and rosettes to inside, between bands with added red bands lined in white; in tondo alternating leaves and lozenges around dot and three circles; exterior: three bands at top of wall, one in mid-wall and two at top of stem; two bands on stem; top of foot glazed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.874)
